name: visDB
description: Database visualization tool that connects to PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite, SQL Server, and MongoDB to generate interactive ERD diagrams. Features   automatic schema introspection, multiple layout algorithms, drag-and-drop positioning, minimap navigation, light/dark themes, undo/redo history, and    export to SVG/PNG/PDF. Includes CLI for headless use.

name: golevel7v2
description: Go library for parsing, encoding, and manipulating HL7 v2.x healthcare messages. Features streaming parser with MLLP support, struct marshaling/unmarshaling via tags, rule-based validation, ACK/NAK generation, and network client/server for HL7 transport.
